{
  "texts": [
    "One complication of working on a flat screen is that the viewing distance to various locations on the screen differs.",
    "This is taken into account when using trigonometry, whether through this tool or otherwise.",
    "Using the tool by Hutton (2019) however still leaves room for some errors, in that it calculates the horizontal and vertical extent of objects separately.",
    "When working with angles instead of Cartesian coordinates, the horizontal and vertical dimensions are no longer independent, which means that the order of the rotations matters.",
    "For a full treatment of this problem in eye tracking and correct solutions, the reader is referred to Haslwanter (1995), or to a set of conversion functions that ship with PsychoPy (https:// psychopy.org/api/tools/monitorunittools.html)."
  ]
}